Insider Activity


Individual




Deryck Charles Maughan



Mr. Deryck C. Maughan is IACFM Member at Federal Reserve Bank of New York, Independent Non-Executive Director at BlackRock, Inc., Senior Independent Non-Executive Director at GlaxoSmithKline Plc, and Independent Non-Executive Director at Genelabs Technologies, Inc. He is on the Board of Directors at BlackRock, Inc., GlaxoSmithKline Plc, Genelabs Technologies, Inc., Carnegie Hall Society, Inc., NYU Langone Medical Center, The Trilateral Commission, Reuters Ltd., and The British Museum.
Mr. Maughan was previously employed as Independent Director by Thomson Reuters Corp., a Member by Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. LP, Chairman by The U.S.-Japan Business Council, Inc., Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Citigroup Global Markets Ltd., Vice Chairman by Citigroup, Inc., Vice Chairman by New York Stock Exchange, Inc., Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Salomon Bros. Asia Ltd., Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Salomon Brothers, Inc., a Member by The Goldman Sachs Group LP, a Member by HM Treasury, and Chairman & Chief Executive Officer by Citigroup International LLC. He also served on the board at Thomson Reuters Plc, The American Academy in Berlin, Reuters Group Plc, and Lincoln Center for the Performing Arts, Inc.
He received his undergraduate degree from King's College London and an undergraduate degree from the Stanford Graduate School of Business.



