Deryck C. Maughan - SourceWatch




















Deryck C. Maughan

From SourceWatch


					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

Sir Deryck C. Maughan "is the Managing Director and Chairman of Asia at Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. He serves as the Managing Director at Nikko Securities Co., Ltd. Sir Maughan served as an Executive President of Citigroup Global Markets Holdings Inc., (formerly, Salomon Inc.) since 1993 to October 2004. He was also a Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Nikko Citigroup Limited. Sir Maughan started at the U.K. Treasury in 1969, moved to Goldman Sachs ten years later, ... and then joined Salomon Brothers. He served as the Chief Executive Officer and Chairman of Salomon Brothers Inc. since May 1992 until October 2004. Sir Maughan served as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Citigroup International. He was elected as a Tokyo Branch Manager at Salomon Brothers Asia, Limited in August 1986 and in January 1988 as the Chairman. Sir Maughan served as the Chief Operating Officer of Salomon Brothers Inc. since August 1991. In November 1997, he was elected as the Co-Chairman and Co-Chief Executive Officer of Salomon Smith Barney, (following the Merger of Salomon Brothers and Smith Barney). Sir Maughan is a Director at Blackrock Inc. and Trustee at Lincoln Center, NYU Medical Center, Carnegie Hall, and the Japan Society. He also serves on Advisory Councils at Harvard and Stanford Universities and serves as a Director of Nikko Securities Co. Ltd, GlaxoSmithKline, and Reuters Group. Sir Maughan also served as the Chairman at Cross-Marketing Group and Citigroup Japan. He was elected as the Vice Chairman of Investment Banking Division at Salomon Brothers in January 1991. Sir Maughan was elected in August 1986 as a Representative Director at Salomon Brothers Asia Ltd. He served as the Vice Chairman of Citigroup Inc. from 1998 until 2004. Sir Maughan served as a Director of Salomon Brothers Inc. and New York City Investment Fund and Director of Citigroup International, Cross-Marketing Group, and Citigroup Japan. He served as a Director of Citigroup Global Markets Holdings Inc. since 1991 and Citigroup Inc. Sir Maughan was the Chairman of the U.S.-Japan Business Council and Vice Chairman of the New York Stock Exchange from 1996 to 2000." [1]

Executive Committee, Trilateral Commission
Advisory Board, Renaissance Weekend

External links

"Deryck C. Maughan", (Biographical note), Undated, Accessed June 2007.




 
